# Native / Capacitor release bundle only (loaded when building with `--mode capacitor`).
# Setup:
#   copy .env.capacitor.example .env.capacitor
# Then set your real HTTPS API host (no trailing slash; must NOT end in /api).
#
# Local emulator: run `npm run dev:server`, then `npm run cap:sync` (uses `.env.capacitor-dev`, not this file).
# Do not put an expired trycloudflare URL here — that breaks every API call on device until you refresh it.
# Physical devices: set a current HTTPS or LAN http origin below, then `npm run cap:sync:release`.
#
# Build + sync native shells:
#   npm run cap:sync:release
#
# Production (Render): https://simvest-api.onrender.com
VITE_API_ORIGIN=https://simvest-api.onrender.com